KSP: .25 Windows 32bit

Problem: No strategies in the administration building.

Mods Installed:

[x] Science! v1.0

FAR v0.14.2

Deadly Reentry v6.0

Better Than Starting Manned

Reproduction Steps: Start a new game, go to the administration building, and notice the lack of available strategies.

Log:

https://www.dropbox.com/s/gehhz7ufp3c3rsy/output_log.txt?dl=0

P.S. I will be away all weekend so if I do not reply, that's why.

In any case, the only obvious errors thrown in the log are from EVE -- try removing that to see if they're related. If that doesn't solve it, I'd run a check through your GameData folder and ensure all your mods are updated & confirmed to be working with 0.25.

I didn't think the graphical mods would be causing a problem so I didn't mention them, and removing EVE does not fix the problem so it looks like I'll just have to check all my mods for updates. Thanks for the help though.

Edited October 11, 2014 by sarge1022
One quick check: you have two versions of ModuleManager. I believe 2.2.0 is one of the few versions where having multiple copies can cause problems.

Thanks I'll try removing 2.20. But after removing my mods one by one, BTSM seems to be the problem. I wonder if anyone else is having this problem.

EDIT: Nope, MM 2.2.0 wasn't the problem, it's definitely BTSM.

Edited October 11, 2014 by sarge1022

I've marked this as solved because it seems to be a problem with Better Than Starting Manned. A fresh install with only BTSM and its dependencies still has the problem.
